==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Argonauta
<hw>Ar`go*nau"ta</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of Cephalopoda. The shell is called
<prod>paper nautilus</prod> or <prod>paper sailor</prod>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The animal has much resemblance to an Octopus. It has
eight arms, two of which are expanded at the end and clasp the shell,
but are never elevated in the air for sails as was formerly supposed.
The creature swims beneath the surface by means of a jet of water, like
other cephalopods. The male has no shell, and is much smaller than the
female. See <er>Hectocotylus</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Argonautic</ent>⟦br⟧
